HEADWORD: Infertility
<hw>In`fer*til"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>infertilitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>infertilit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The state or quality of being infertile; unproductiveness;
barrenness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>infertility</qex> or noxiousness of the soil.</q>
